  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Planner",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in the preparation, updating, and maintenance of project schedules under the supervision of senior planners or schedulers.</li>\n  <li>Input schedule data into scheduling software such as Primavera P6 or Microsoft Project.</li>\n  <li>Work with project teams to gather schedule information on design, procurement, construction, and commissioning activities.</li>\n  <li>Help monitor project progress and update timelines accordingly.</li>\n  <li>Support the generation of weekly and monthly schedule reports and look-ahead plans.</li>\n  <li>Maintain schedule documentation and ensure activity coding and Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) are properly applied.</li>\n  <li>Track progress of subcontractor activities and coordinate updates to the master schedule.</li>\n  <li>Attend internal meetings and take notes for action items and scheduling updates.</li>\n  <li>Support analysis of schedule delays and assist in the development of recovery plans.</li>\n  <li>Apply basic scheduling concepts, including critical path, float, and dependencies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma with at least 1 year of experience in project scheduling/planning support, preferably in data centre or critical environment.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of scheduling tools such as Primavera P6 or Microsoft Project.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with construction sequences and project lifecycles.</li>\n  <li>Certification in workplace safety (eg. WSQ, WSH) preferred.</li>\n  <li>Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</li>\n  <li>Team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, communication and collaborative skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
